TextChange: But there is more to the American Dream

The great \"American Dream\" has always been having a good job, being able to afford things, and living a great life.  The basis for that dream is the concept of money and spending that money to live a life.  That being said, is there anything wrong with having materialistic dreams?  Why are we so quick to judge and criticize people for buying things and striving for material posession.  I believe that is nothing wrong with having materialistic goals and we should not criticize people for wanting to buy, collect, and have possessions.   => The great \"American Dream\" has always been having a good job, being able to afford things, and living a great life. \nAmerican society is built on the idea of wealth.
How do we get those things - working.

Where materialistism gets criticism is collecting posssions and things for the sole purpose of showing them off, being boastful.  Materialism is different from being boastful though.  Collecting things to show off should be critizcized, it is using your posessions to inflict emotional pain on people.  Materialism is not boastful though - wanting to have things in order to live is not being boastful.
